{"name": "python-rektor-monitor", "metadata": {"name": "python-rektor-monitor", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["requests", "cryptography"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733090395}, "documentation": ["# Python Rekor Monitor Template\n\n## Prerequisite:\n- Install cosign: https://docs.sigstore.dev/cosign/system_config/installation/\n\n## Steps:\n1. Sign an artifact using cosign tool with your identity using:\n```bash\n    cosign sign-blob <file> --bundle cosign.bundle\n  ```\nMore info on signing blobs is here: https://docs.sigstore.dev/cosign/signing/signing_with_blobs/\n\n2. Fetch latest checkpoints from Rekor log using:\n```bash\n    rekor-monitor -c\n  ```\n\n3. Verify that the artifact signature in the transparency log is correct and verify that the log entry is included in the latest checkpoint of the transparency log by verifying the inclusion Proof merkle proof\n```bash\n    rekor-monitor --inclusion <logIndex of signed artifact> --artifact <artifact file>\n  ```\n\n4. Verify that the checkpoint which had our entry added is consistent with the latest checkpoint using the checkpoint details obtained in step 2.\n```bash\n    rekor-monitor --consistency --tree-id <treeid in latest checkpoint> --tree-size <treesize in latest checkpoint> --root-hash <roothash in latest checkpoint>\n  ```\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main", "documentation": ["Homework 1 Software Supply Chain Security"], "functions": [{"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.get_log_entry", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "log_index", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["fetches certificate info from rekor transparency log API when given log index"]}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.get_verification_proof", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "log_index", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["checks if log index is sane"]}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.inclusion", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "log_index", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "artifact_filepath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "debug", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["extracts signature and public key, uses it to verify signature and merkle proof"]}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.get_latest_checkpoint", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["fetches checkpoint from transparency log"]}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.consistency", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "prev_checkpoint", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["verify consistency between an older and latest checkpoint"]}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["parses through cli arguments and calls either to verify entry and signature inclusion or checkpoint consistency"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.util", "documentation": ["functions to support Verify entry inclusion and artifact signature present in transparency log"], "functions": [{"name": "python_rekor_monitor.util.extract_public_key", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cert", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "python_rekor_monitor.util.verify_artifact_signature", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "signature", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "public_key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "artifact_filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": 